Amcast Industrial Corp. said it plans to repurchase 500,000 shares, or about 7% of its shares outstanding, in open market transactions.
The metal products concern currently has 7.2 million common shares outstanding. 

Amcast previously had said it planned to repurchase shares, but didn't disclose when or how many shares it intended to buy back.
The company named Dillon Read & Co. as its exclusive agent for the stock buy-back program. 

